		<item>
		<title>Announcing MidoNet Mini-Summit Tokyo (October 26)</title>
		<link>https://blog.midonet.org/announcing-midonet-mini-summit-tokyo-october-26/</link>
		<comments>https://blog.midonet.org/announcing-midonet-mini-summit-tokyo-october-26/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Tue, 01 Sep 2015 04:42:18 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Sandro Mathys]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Community]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Event]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[OpenStack]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Mini-Summit]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Tokyo]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[Training]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://blog.midonet.org/?p=482</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p>[Update: MidoNet Mini-Summit has since been renamed MidoDay Tokyo 2015] We&#8217;re happy to announce the first-ever MidoNet Mini-Summit! If you&#8217;re going to the OpenStack Summit Tokyo, this is an ideal chance for you to meet fellow operators and our developers. Of course, you&#8217;ll also learn about the current state of MidoNet, get an outlook of what <a class="read-more" href="https://blog.midonet.org/announcing-midonet-mini-summit-tokyo-october-26/">&#8230;&#160;<span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a></p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://blog.midonet.org/announcing-midonet-mini-summit-tokyo-october-26/">Announcing MidoNet Mini-Summit Tokyo (October 26)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://blog.midonet.org">The MidoNet Blog</a>.</p>
]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>[Update: MidoNet Mini-Summit has since been renamed MidoDay Tokyo 2015]</p>
<p>We&#8217;re happy to announce the first-ever MidoNet Mini-Summit! If you&#8217;re going to the OpenStack Summit Tokyo, this is an ideal chance for you to meet fellow operators and our developers. Of course, you&#8217;ll also learn about the current state of MidoNet, get an outlook of what to expect next, and much more. For beginners, we even offer half a day of hands-on training from our experts!</p>
<p><a href="http://www.eventbrite.com/e/midonet-mini-summit-tickets-18235379511"><img class="size-full wp-image-485 aligncenter" src="https://i0.wp.com/blog.midonet.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/09/mini-summit-tokyo.png?resize=300%2C150" alt="MidoNet Mini-Summit Tokyo" data-recalc-dims="1" /></a></p>
<p>If you&#8217;re interested, please mark your calendar on Monday, October 26 (i.e. the day before the OpenStack Summit) and register <a href="http://www.eventbrite.com/e/midonet-mini-summit-tickets-18235379511" target="_blank">here</a>! Participation is free of charge, just the hands-on training costs a nominal fee of USD 50 (plus a booking fee of USD 3.74) to cover some of our costs.</p>
<p>Note, that we&#8217;re still in the early planning phase and that&#8217;s why you can help shape the event by taking part in our <a href="http://goo.gl/forms/79ka9e2fgB" target="_blank">quick survey</a>. Also, if you have a story to share and would like to present at our Mini-Summit, don&#8217;t hesitate to drop <a href="mailto:sandro@midokura.com">Sandro</a> a line!</p>
<p>Last but not least, if you can&#8217;t make it to Tokyo this time, stay tuned: the MidoNet Mini-Summit is going global in 2016!</p>
<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://blog.midonet.org/announcing-midonet-mini-summit-tokyo-october-26/">Announcing MidoNet Mini-Summit Tokyo (October 26)</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://blog.midonet.org">The MidoNet Blog</a>.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
